cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

The paper discusses video streaming over distributed storage, which involves networking and communication aspects, making cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) the most likely category. The paper also discusses video encoding and quality selection, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The optimization problem formulation and solution involve decision-making and control, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses probability distributions and characterizes the download time of video segments, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
